Senior Software Engineer

Opus Recruitment Solutions London Area, United Kingdom On-site

Meet the hiring team

Joseph Gough
3rd
Recruiting all things Java in London
Job poster

About the job

My client are a leading provider of cutting-edge software and AI solutions. Their mission is to revolutionize industries through advanced technology, utilizing a combination of Java, Kotlin, React, JavaScript, MongoDB, Machine Learning, and Azure cloud services. They are dedicated to pushing the boundaries of what's possible and delivering impactful solutions to their clients.


Position Overview:

They are seeking a highly skilled Senior Software Developer to join their talented team. As a Senior Software Developer, you will play a crucial role in designing, developing, and implementing software solutions that leverage the latest technologies to address complex challenges in various industries.


Responsibilities:
  • Collaborate with cross-functional teams to gather and analyse requirements, and translate them into technical specifications and solutions.
  • Design and develop robust, scalable, and efficient software applications using Java, Kotlin, React, JavaScript, MongoDB, and other relevant technologies.
  • Implement machine learning algorithms and integrate AI capabilities into software solutions to enhance performance and functionality.
  • Work closely with DevOps teams to ensure smooth deployment and operation of software solutions on Azure cloud services.
  • Conduct code reviews, mentor junior team members, and contribute to the continuous improvement of development processes and best practices.
  • Stay up-to-date with the latest advancements in software development, AI, and related technologies, and recommend innovative approaches to enhance our offerings.


Qualifications:
  • Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.
  • Extensive experience (5+ years) in software development, with a strong proficiency in Java, Kotlin, React, JavaScript, and MongoDB.
  • Solid understanding of machine learning concepts and experience in applying ML algorithms to real-world problems.
  • Hands-on experience with cloud platforms, preferably Azure, and expertise in deploying and managing applications on cloud infrastructure.
  • Strong problem-solving skills, attention to detail, and ability to work effectively in a fast-paced environment.
  • Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams.


Benefits:
  • Competitive salary and comprehensive benefits package.
  • Opportunity to work on cutting-edge projects and make a significant impact in various industries.
  • Continuous learning and professional development opportunities.
  • Collaborative and inclusive work culture that values creativity, innovation, and diversity.

About the company

Opus Recruitment Solutions
491,384 followers
Staffing and Recruiting 201-500 employees

At Opus Recruitment Solutions we thrive on excellence, priding ourselves on being young, vibrant, creative and fast growing, as a specialist IT and Engineering recruitment solutions consultancy.

We operate on an international scale in New York, London, Sydney, Amsterdam, Hong Kong, Manchester & Bristol. We service the needs of our clients and candidates across a multitude of vacancies through top tier solutions which have placed us on a number of PSLs. Our annual compound growth is in excess of 70% as a result of our high quality recruitment offering.

Professionalism is at the core of everything we do. Our dynamic team are friendly and specialist recruitment consultants who are highly experienced in their niche markets.
